<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-22T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="947" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d947">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-22T18:00:00-04:00">July 22,
                                    1949—6 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>871. Urtel 1571 July 21. Since any statement made by Dept re “shop
                            guarantee” and ur departure wld be designed for Chi consumption rather
                            than world or US, Dept desires you prepare and forward soonest draft
                            statement for release by Dept when you feel time propitious or when
                            negative reply recd from Commies. Statement shld be designed facilitate
                            ur own departure as well as future movements US cit[izen]s desiring
                            leave or travel within China.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>